                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48/2930: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-01T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 1, 1918—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6482. For Hurley. Your number 2. President agrees with your position and asks
                    that you confer immediately with Colonel House explaining to him that the aspect
                    stated in your telegram was one which the President had not taken into account
                    in assenting to House’s suggested communication to the Supreme War Council.</p>
                <p>For the Ambassador. Please advise Colonel House of foregoing as soon as
                    possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
